From: R9700 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-11
Subject: [PATCH] moe_wna16: accept gelu activation alongside silu

The Triton fused MoE kernel in
`sglang/srt/layers/moe/moe_runner/triton_utils/fused_moe.py` (lines ~528,
564, 588, 590) supports BOTH silu and gelu activations, but
`MoeWNA16Method.apply()` hardcodes a `== "silu"` assertion that
short-circuits gelu before the kernel sees it.  This blocks Gemma 4 26B
MoE on RDNA4 — the experts ship with `activation="gelu"` (Gemma 4 uses
gelu_pytorch_tanh end-to-end).  Without this patch, gemma4 launch fails
with `AssertionError: Only SiLU activation is supported.` from
`moe_wna16.py:388`.

Same model also requires:
- patches/023 (gemma4-moe-mlp-no-quant-config) for the dense-MLP load
- patches/024 (gemma4-mm-towers-no-quant-config) for vision tower BF16
- patches/034 (gemma4-mm-per-expert-awq-mapping) for AWQ MoE expert load
- launch.sh QUANT="moe_wna16" to force the AWQ MoE method (because
  AWQConfig.get_quant_method returns None for FusedMoE on non-NPU)

Root-caused 2026-05-11 via top-down NaN bisect on R9700.  See
project_gemma4_v0511_root_cause.md memory for the full chain.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/moe_wna16.py b/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/moe_wna16.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/moe_wna16.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/moe_wna16.py
@@ -384,9 +384,13 @@ class MoeWNA16Method(FusedMoEMethodBase):
         layer: torch.nn.Module,
         dispatch_output: StandardDispatchOutput,
     ) -> CombineInput:
-        assert (
-            self.moe_runner_config.activation == "silu"
-        ), "Only SiLU activation is supported."
+        # Triton fused MoE in moe_runner/triton_utils/fused_moe.py supports both
+        # silu and gelu (lines ~528/564/588/590), so accept either. Required by
+        # Gemma 4 26B MoE on RDNA4 — the experts use `activation="gelu"`.
+        assert self.moe_runner_config.activation in (
+            "silu",
+            "gelu",
+        ), f"Only SiLU/GeLU activation is supported, got {self.moe_runner_config.activation!r}."

         quant_info = self.get_triton_quant_info(layer)
         return self.runner.run(dispatch_output, quant_info)
